🛒 Lifestyle Store – Full Stack Web Development Project

This is a full-stack e-commerce web application built using PHP, MySQL, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, and JavaScript.
It was developed as part of an Internshala Full Stack Web Development project.

✨ Features

🔐 User Authentication – Sign Up, Login, Logout, Session Management

👕 Product Catalog – Browse products like watches, shirts, cameras

🛍️ Add to Cart & Order Management – Add items, place orders, track purchases

👤 User Profile Management – Update account details and view order history

📧 Contact & Messaging – Send queries via contact form

🎨 Responsive UI – Designed with Bootstrap for mobile-first experience

🗄️ Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap, JavaScript

Backend: PHP 7+

Database: MySQL (phpMyAdmin)

Server: Apache (via XAMPP)

⚙️ Setup Instructions

Install XAMPP (Apache + MySQL).

Start Apache and MySQL from the XAMPP Control Panel.

Copy this project folder into:

C:\xampp\htdocs\estore


Open phpMyAdmin
.

Create a new database:

lifestylestoresql


Import the SQL file from this repo (lifestylestoresql.sql).

In browser, open:

http://localhost/estore/

📂 Folder Structure
estore/
│── css/             → Stylesheets
│── img/             → Images
│── includes/        → Common PHP includes (DB connection, header, footer)
│── index.php        → Homepage
│── products.php     → Product listing
│── cart.php         → Shopping cart
│── signup.php       → User registration
│── login.php        → User login
│── lifestylestoresql.sql → Database export

